{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17474889","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17474889"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-28T22:26:01+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-28T22:26:01+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"12440"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}},{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17583677","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17583677"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T07:24:19+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T07:24:19+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"12440"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"12440","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/12440"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.06,0.77,0.06,0.02,0.08]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"4948"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"108155"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"4948","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/4948"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"12440"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"90567"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"9"},{"type":"tags","id":"11"},{"type":"tags","id":"42"},{"type":"tags","id":"64"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"4947"},{"type":"tags","id":"5326"},{"type":"tags","id":"11181"},{"type":"tags","id":"11199"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"8117"},{"type":"contributions","id":"9372"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"108155","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/108155"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA standard screening process is performed on a neonate and is subsequently discovered to have one DNA mutation and a positive immunoreactive trypsinogen test.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the appropriate next investigation?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["No further investigations needed","Sweat chloride test and extended DNA analysis","Repeat the immunoreactive trypsinogen and DNA assays","Serum and urine chloride estimation","Serum amylase, lipase, and trypsin"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":[],"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe concern is that this neonate might have cystic fibrosis. A positive immunoreactive trypsinogen result is followed by DNA mutation analysis. Detection of one mutation cannot be used to diagnose cystic fibrosis. Follow-up testing by measuring \u003Cstrong\u003Esweat chloride and extended DNA analysis\u003C/strong\u003E is used to confirm the diagnosis of cystic fibrosis. \u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EA positive immunoreactive trypsinogen result followed by the detection of two disease-causing mutations is strongly suggestive of cystic fibrosis. In this case, an elevated sweat chloride result will confirm the diagnosis of cystic fibrosis. A positive immunoreactive trypsinogen result followed by a negative DNA mutation result requires another blood sample to be taken three weeks later and the immunoreactive trypsinogen and DNA mutation assays repeated. A negative immunoreactive trypsinogen result with a negative DNA mutation result in a second blood sample suggests that the positive immunoreactive trypsinogen result obtained in the first sample was a false-positive result. \u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESerum amylase, lipase, trypsin, chloride, and urine chloride testing \u003C/strong\u003Eare not recommended in the evaluation of cystic fibrosis.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Diagnosing CF is a multistep process.","A complete diagnostic evaluation should include a newborn screening, a sweat chloride test, a genetic or carrier test, and clinical evaluation."],"references":["Coverstone, A. M., \u0026 Ferkol, T. W. (2021). Early Diagnosis and Intervention in Cystic Fibrosis: Imagining the Unimaginable. Frontiers in Pediatrics, 8.","Cystic Fibrosis - Genomics in general practice. Royal Australian College of General Practitioners. December 2023. Available from: https://www.racgp.org.au/getattachment/63568f23-e288-4a0e-a23a-39fbd046cc21/Genomics-in-general-practice.aspx"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"90567"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"12440"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"90567","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/90567"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-07-07T10:12:49+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-07-07T10:12:49+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"4948"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"108155"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"9","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/9"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udc76","name":"Paediatrics","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-01-16T08:39:03+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"11","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/11"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\udec1","name":"Respiratory Medicine","synonyms":["Pulmonology"],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"42",